    "statementHTML": "<div class=\"statement-body\">\n<div class=\"statement-section statement-goal\">\n   <h2><span class=\"icon icon-goal\">&nbsp;</span><span>Goal </span></h2>\n   <span class=\"question-statement\">A bookshelf contains <var>N</var> books arranged in a row. Each book starts in one of three positions: upright (<const>|</const>), leaning left (<const>\\</const>), or leaning right (<const>/</const>).<br><br>● A book that's leaning left will push on the book <strong>directly to its left</strong>, causing that book to <strong>lean left</strong> if it was previously upright. For example, <const>|\\</const> &rarr; <const>\\\\</const>.<br>● A book that's leaning right will push on the book <strong>directly to its right</strong>, causing that book to <strong>lean right</strong> if it was previously upright. For example, <const>/|</const> &rarr; <const>//</const>.<br>● Books pushing on each other or getting pushed on with <strong>opposing forces</strong> will <strong>stop moving</strong> (no change in position). For example, <const>/\\</const> &rarr; <const>/\\</const> and <const>/|\\</const> &rarr; <const>/|\\</const>.<br><br>The books are allowed to lean on one another from their starting positions until all of the books stop moving. Given the starting positions of the books, what will the bookshelf look like at the end?</span>\n</div>\n<div class=\"statement-section statement-protocol\">\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Input</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-input\"><strong>Line 1</strong>: A single positive integer <var>N</var>; the number of books.<br><strong>Line 2</strong>: <var>N</var> characters denoting the books on the bookshelf. Each character is one of <const>|</const>, <const>\\</const>, or <const>/</const>.</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Output</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-output\"><strong>Line 1</strong>: <var>N</var> characters denoting the final positions of the books.</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Constraints</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-constraints\">1 &le; <var>N</var> &le; 1000</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Example</div>\n      <div class=\"statement-inout\">\n         <div class=\"statement-inout-in\">\n            <div class=\"title\">Input</div>\n            <pre class=\"question-statement-example-in\">9\n|||\\|/|||</pre>\n         </div>\n         <div class=\"statement-inout-out\">\n            <div class=\"title\">Output</div>\n            <pre class=\"question-statement-example-out\">\\\\\\\\|////</pre>\n         </div>\n      </div>\n   </div>\n</div>"
